events.title: Economic Calendar Event - Q1 2024
events.description: The Federal Reserve announced today that it will maintain its current monetary policy stance.

events.title: ECB Interest Rate Decision
events.description: The European Central Bank has decided to increase interest rates by 25 basis points in response to persistent inflation pressures.

events.title: US Employment Report
events.description: Non-farm payrolls increased by 223,000 in December, exceeding market expectations of 200,000 jobs.

events.title: Bank of Japan Policy Meeting
events.description: The Bank of Japan maintains negative interest rates while adjusting yield curve control parameters.

events.title: UK Inflation Data Release
events.description: British consumer price inflation unexpectedly slowed to 3.9% in November from 4.6% in October.
